  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Mix gochujang, soy sauce, brown sugar, sesame oil, salt, and black pepper in a bowl.",
    "Chop 4-6 garlic cloves and add them to the bowl. Toss to coat.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a small cast-iron skillet or a baking dish and spread evenly.",
    "Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the garlic is charred and caramelized, stirring occasionally.",
    "Stir in 2 tbsp of sour cream.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning with salt, black pepper, and more gochujang if needed.",
    "Garnish with chopped green onions and toasted sesame seeds.",
    "Serve warm over rice, noodles, or enjoy as a solo-dinner."
  ],
